This article is a press gaggle by Press Secretary Robert Gibbs aboard Air Force One. In the gaggle, Gibbs discusses the reasons for President Obama's trip to New Orleans, the weather conditions affecting their schedule, and the updates on the oil spill in the Gulf. He also mentions that John Brennan, Assistant to the President for Homeland Security and Counterterrorism, has been briefed on the situation in New York and is coordinating with the FBI and NYPD. Gibbs mentions that efforts are being made to cap the well and deal with the oil that has already spread. He also mentions that the President is meeting with various individuals in Venice, Louisiana to address the urgent situation. The article concludes with a mention of the ongoing Supreme Court process and the possibility of the President making remarks on the New York incident.